
[1]sweetness

   SWEE'TNESS, n. The quality of being sweet, in any of its senses; as
   gratefulness to the taste; or to the smell,fragrance; agreeableness to
   the ear, melody; as sweetness of the voice; sweetness of elocution.

   1. Agreeableness of manners; softness; mildness; obliging civility; as
   sweetness of behavior.

   2. Softness; mildness; amiableness; as sweetness of temper.
